274.content:
Originally published at July 11th 2019

INTRODUCTION

What is #AI?
Do you think AI is Artificial Intelligence?
Nope, this AI stands for Ayyub-Isa, two of my incredible sons, love them so much, both of them.

AI is personal system, based on #console.
Built to make communication safer. No spying shit!
Writen in C, but after all, I finally decided to use PHP as the framework from C, to make the scripts more efficient to write.
Functionalities of AI are to manage communication encrypted, to keep your data safe, and many more useful packages are ready to be installed.


REQUIREMENTS

- Operating System: Linux (Debian/Ubuntu/CentOS/RHEL/Fendora/Arch/Manjaro), Windows (7, 8, 8.1, 10), Android (OS 5 or greater with Termux installed)
- Disk space: Estimated to 65 MB tops (all packages are installed)
- Empty directory path, C:\9r3i\ai (Windows), /9r3i/ai (Linux), /sdcard/9r3i/ai (Termux)
- PHP version 5.6.x or higher. Recommended version is 7.3.x (as AI version >= 2.0.0)


PREPARATION

Install PHP in Windows:
- Download at: https://windows.php.net/, Create path to it, so PHP can easily called from CMD.

Install PHP in Linux: @[locode[
# Ubuntu/Debian
$ sudo apt install php-cli php-common php-zlib php-zip php-sqlite3 php-sockets php-openssl php-mbstring php-json php-gd php-curl php-calendar php-readline

# Fendora
$ sudo dnf install php-cli php-common php-zlib php-zip php-sqlite3 php-sockets php-openssl php-mbstring php-json php-gd php-curl php-calendar php-readline

# CentOS/RHEL
$ sudo yum install php-cli php-common php-zlib php-zip php-sqlite3 php-sockets php-openssl php-mbstring php-json php-gd php-curl php-calendar php-readline

# Arch Linux/Manjaro
$ sudo pacman -S php-cli php-common php-zlib php-zip php-sqlite3 php-sockets php-openssl php-mbstring php-json php-gd php-curl php-calendar php-readline
~]]
Install PHP in Termux: @[locode[
$ pkg install php
~]]


INSTALLATION

Simply copy this code and paste in console: CMD (Windows) or TERMUX (Android) or TERMINAL (Linux).
@[locode:php[
/* -------CODE START------- */
php -a
$url='files/ai/setup.ai';
if(!function_exists('gzinflate')){
  exit("Status: [ERROR] Require zlib extension.");
}$file='install.ai';
$get=@file_get_contents($url.'?r='.mt_rand());
$put=@file_put_contents($file,gzinflate($get));
$push="\r\n\r\n\t";
$out=["\r\n\r\n"];
if(!$put){
  @unlink($file);
  $out[]="Status: [ERROR] Failed to get script.";
  $out[]="Type  : exit";
}else{
  $out[]="Status: [OK] Ready to execute script.";
  $out[]="Type  : exit";
  $out[]="Then  : php install.ai";
}$out[]="\r\n\r\n";
echo implode($push,$out);

/* -------CODE END------- */
  
~]]
Note: Change the url in code with another url below if failed to get script.
- files/ai/setup.ai
- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/9r3i/ai/master/setup.ai
If still failed to download, make sure that file "cacert.pem" is in the right place.


USER GUIDE

Once the installation is successful, restart computer. Then open console CMD (Windows), Teminal (Linux) or Termux (Android), and type:
@[locode[
$ ai help
~]]
Everything is in there. Enjoy!
Visit https://github.com/9r3i/ai/ for more updates and information.
